A New Hampshire mother says her son is “traumatized” after a man apparently “triggered” by the 15-year-old’s “Make America Great Again” hat slapped him across the face at a polling site earlier this week.
“I was apprehensive about him wearing the MAGA hat, because we know it can provoke and we know people don’t like Trump,” she said.
“But he wore the hat because he’s a proud 15-year-old and he doesn’t know what people are going to be like.
He is also accused of throwing Trump campaign signs and attempting to knock over the campaign tent, police said.
